commit.message: Workaround till travis gets a newer pypy.

log "cry" messages to "remote_pdb" instead of the root logger

By configuring "cry" messages to use the "remote_pdb" logger instead of the
root logger, a consumer can suppress duplicate messages if the root logger is
also configured to log to STDERR

commit.message: Also make sure virtualenv is recentish.
Fix a bunch of skel issues. Disable coveralls.
Add REMOTE_PDB_QUIET=1 to allow silencing output

make quit behaviour consistent with pdb

on quit, pdb will raise `BdbQuit`.
Rework the patch to be simpler and add an integration test for this bug.

Fix for Python 3.6.7 to 3.8a2, where the read buffer was emptied
when data is sent. This prevented multiple rapidly entered commands
from all being received, causing failing tests and the inability
to paste commands into the telnet window.
Update tox set up to run on modern versions of Python
